# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Supabase migration environment variables
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Copy this file to scripts/migrate.env (already in .gitignore) and fill in
# the values before running any `make export / import / update-config` targets.
#
# Where to find these values in the Supabase dashboard:
#   URL + anon key:      Project Settings → API → Project URL / anon public
#   service_role key:    Project Settings → API → service_role secret  ← KEEP SECRET
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# ── OLD project (the one being migrated away from) ───────────────────────────
# Leave blank if you are importing from a backup file without needing to
# connect to the old project (e.g. it is already paused/deleted).
OLD_SUPABASE_URL=https://OLD_REF.supabase.co
OLD_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY=

# ── NEW project (the freshly created replacement) ────────────────────────────
NEW_SUPABASE_URL=https://NEW_REF.supabase.co
NEW_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY=
NEW_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=
